Function along with it's lexical scope bundled together is called closures.

function x(){
  var a = 73
  function (y){
    console. log(a):
  }
  return y;
}
var z = x();
console.log (z);
z();


// 73

Uses of closures :
- Module design Pattern
-Currying
-Functions like once
-Memoize
-Mainting state in aysnc world
-setTimeout
-Iterators
